{"paragraphs":[{"cues":[{"time":0,"text":"What is bioenergy? Bioenergy is not ethanol."},{"time":6000,"text":"Bioenergy isn't global warming. Bioenergy is"},{"time":12000,"text":"something which seems counterintuitive. Bioenergy"},{"time":14000,"text":"is oil. It's gas. It's coal. And part of building"},{"time":19000,"text":"that bridge to the future, to the point where we"},{"time":21000,"text":"can actually see the oceans in a rational way, or"},{"time":24000,"text":"put up these geo-spatial orbits that will twirl or"},{"time":29000,"text":"do microwaves or stuff, is going to depend on how"},{"time":32000,"text":"we understand bioenergy and manage it. And to do"},{"time":35000,"text":"that, you really have to look first at agriculture."}]},{"cues":[{"time":38000,"text":"So we've been planting stuff for 11,000 years. And"},{"time":42000,"text":"in the measure that we plant stuff, what we learn"},{"time":45000,"text":"from agriculture is you've got to deal with pests,"},{"time":48000,"text":"you've got to deal with all types of awful things,"},{"time":51000,"text":"you've got to cultivate stuff. In the measure"},{"time":52000,"text":"that you learn how to use water to cultivate, then"},{"time":56000,"text":"you're going to be able to spread beyond the Nile."},{"time":59000,"text":"You're going to be able to power stuff, so irrigation"},{"time":62000,"text":"makes a difference."}]},{"cues":[{"time":64000,"text":"Irrigation starts to make you be allowed to plant"},{"time":66000,"text":"stuff where you want it, as opposed to where the"},{"time":69000,"text":"rivers flood. You start getting this organic"},{"time":71000,"text":"agriculture; you start putting machinery onto this"},{"time":75000,"text":"stuff. Machinery, with a whole bunch of water,"},{"time":78000,"text":"leads to very large-scale agriculture."},{"time":81000,"text":"You put together machines and water, and you get"},{"time":85000,"text":"landscapes that look like this. And then you get"},{"time":89000,"text":"sales that look like this. It's brute force. So"},{"time":93000,"text":"what you've been doing in agriculture is you start"},{"time":95000,"text":"out with something that's a reasonably natural"},{"time":97000,"text":"system. You start taming that natural system. You"},{"time":99000,"text":"put a lot of force behind that natural system. You"},{"time":102000,"text":"put a whole bunch of pesticides and herbicides --"},{"time":106000,"text":"(Laughter) -- behind that natural system, and you"},{"time":114000,"text":"end up with systems that look like this."}]},{"cues":[{"time":118000,"text":"And it's all brute force. And that's the way we've"},{"time":121000,"text":"been approaching energy. So the lesson in"},{"time":124000,"text":"agriculture is that you can actually change the"},{"time":127000,"text":"system that's based on brute force as you start"},{"time":130000,"text":"merging that system and learning that system and"},{"time":132000,"text":"actually applying biology. And you move from a"},{"time":135000,"text":"discipline of engineering, you move from a"},{"time":137000,"text":"discipline of chemistry, into a discipline of"},{"time":139000,"text":"biology. And probably one of the most important"},{"time":143000,"text":"human beings on the planet is this guy behind me."}]},{"cues":[{"time":146000,"text":"This is a guy called Norman Borlaug. He won the"},{"time":148000,"text":"Nobel Prize. He's got the Congressional Medal of"},{"time":150000,"text":"Honor. He deserves all of this stuff. And he"},{"time":154000,"text":"deserves this stuff because he probably has fed"},{"time":156000,"text":"more people than any other human being alive"},{"time":159000,"text":"because he researched how to put biology behind"},{"time":162000,"text":"seeds. He did this in Mexico. The reason why India"},{"time":167000,"text":"and China no longer have these massive famines is"},{"time":170000,"text":"because Norman Borlaug taught them how to grow"},{"time":172000,"text":"grains in a more efficient way and launched the"},{"time":175000,"text":"Green Revolution. That is something that a lot of"},{"time":178000,"text":"people have criticized. But of course, those are"},{"time":179000,"text":"people who don't realize that China and India,"},{"time":182000,"text":"instead of having huge amounts of starving people,"},{"time":185000,"text":"are exporting grains."}]},{"cues":[{"time":187000,"text":"And the irony of this particular system is the"},{"time":189000,"text":"place where he did the research, which was Mexico,"},{"time":192000,"text":"didn't adopt this technology, ignored this"},{"time":194000,"text":"technology, talked about why this technology"},{"time":197000,"text":"should be thought about, but not really applied."},{"time":199000,"text":"And Mexico remains one of the largest grain"},{"time":202000,"text":"importers on the planet because it doesn't apply"},{"time":205000,"text":"technology that was discovered in Mexico. And in"},{"time":208000,"text":"fact, hasn't recognized this man, to the point"},{"time":210000,"text":"where there aren't statues of this man all over"},{"time":213000,"text":"Mexico. There are in China and India. And the"},{"time":216000,"text":"Institute that this guy ran has now moved to"},{"time":218000,"text":"India. That is the difference between adopting"},{"time":222000,"text":"technologies and discussing technologies."},{"time":225000,"text":"Now, it's not just that this guy fed a huge amount"},{"time":229000,"text":"of people in the world. It's that this is the net"},{"time":232000,"text":"effect in terms of what technology does, if you"},{"time":235000,"text":"understand biology."}]},{"cues":[{"time":238000,"text":"What happened in agriculture? Well, if you take"},{"time":239000,"text":"agriculture over a century, agriculture in about"},{"time":242000,"text":"1900 would have been recognizable to somebody"},{"time":245000,"text":"planting a thousand years earlier. Yeah, the plows look"},{"time":248000,"text":"different. The machines were tractors or stuff"},{"time":252000,"text":"instead of mules, but the farmer would have"},{"time":255000,"text":"understood: this is what the guy's doing, this is"},{"time":257000,"text":"why he's doing it, this is where he's going. What"},{"time":260000,"text":"really started to change in agriculture is when"},{"time":262000,"text":"you started moving from this brute force"},{"time":264000,"text":"engineering and chemistry into biology, and that's"},{"time":266000,"text":"where you get your productivity increases. And as"},{"time":269000,"text":"you do that stuff, here's what happens to"},{"time":272000,"text":"productivity."}]},{"cues":[{"time":273000,"text":"Basically, you go from 250 hours to produce 100"},{"time":276000,"text":"bushels, to 40, to 15, to five. Agricultural labor"},{"time":281000,"text":"productivity increased seven times, 1950 to 2000,"},{"time":286000,"text":"whereas the rest of the economy increased about"},{"time":288000,"text":"2.5 times. This is an absolutely massive increase"},{"time":289000,"text":"in how much is produced per person."},{"time":295000,"text":"The effect of this, of course, is it's not just"},{"time":297000,"text":"amber waves of grain, it is mountains of stuff."},{"time":301000,"text":"And 50 percent of the EU budget is going to subsidize"},{"time":303000,"text":"agriculture from mountains of stuff that people"},{"time":306000,"text":"have overproduced."}]},{"cues":[{"time":309000,"text":"This would be a good outcome for energy. And of"},{"time":312000,"text":"course, by now, you're probably saying to"},{"time":314000,"text":"yourself, \"Self, I thought I came to a talk about"},{"time":319000,"text":"energy and here's this guy talking about biology.\""},{"time":324000,"text":"So where's the link between these two things?"},{"time":327000,"text":"One of the ironies of this whole system is we're"},{"time":329000,"text":"discussing what to do about a system that we don't"},{"time":331000,"text":"understand. We don't even know what oil is. We"},{"time":336000,"text":"don't know where oil comes from. I mean,"},{"time":338000,"text":"literally, it's still a source of debate what"},{"time":340000,"text":"this black river of stuff is and where it comes"},{"time":343000,"text":"from. The best assumption, and one of the best"},{"time":346000,"text":"guesses in this stuff, is that this stuff comes"},{"time":349000,"text":"out of this stuff, that these things absorb"},{"time":353000,"text":"sunlight, rot under pressure for millions of"},{"time":356000,"text":"years, and you get these black rivers."}]},{"cues":[{"time":361000,"text":"Now, the interesting thing about that thesis -- if"},{"time":363000,"text":"that thesis turns out to be true -- is that oil,"},{"time":367000,"text":"and all hydrocarbons, turned out to be"},{"time":369000,"text":"concentrated sunlight. And if you think of"},{"time":373000,"text":"bioenergy, bioenergy isn't ethanol. Bioenergy is"},{"time":376000,"text":"taking the sun, concentrating it in amoebas,"},{"time":379000,"text":"concentrating it in plants, and maybe that's why"},{"time":382000,"text":"you get these rainbows."},{"time":385000,"text":"And as you're looking at this system, if"},{"time":388000,"text":"hydrocarbons are concentrated sunlight, then"},{"time":392000,"text":"bioenergy works in a different way. And we've got"},{"time":396000,"text":"to start thinking of oil and other hydrocarbons as"},{"time":400000,"text":"part of these solar panels."},{"time":404000,"text":"Maybe that's one of the reasons why if you fly"},{"time":406000,"text":"over west Texas, the types of wells that you're"},{"time":410000,"text":"beginning to see don't look unlike those pictures"},{"time":414000,"text":"of Kansas and those irrigated plots."}]},{"cues":[{"time":418000,"text":"This is how you farm oil. And as you think of"},{"time":420000,"text":"farming oil and how oil has evolved, we started"},{"time":424000,"text":"with this brute force approach. And then what did"},{"time":428000,"text":"we learn? Then we learned we had to go bigger. And"},{"time":431000,"text":"then what'd we learn? Then we have to go even"},{"time":434000,"text":"bigger. And we are getting really destructive as"},{"time":438000,"text":"we're going out and farming this bioenergy."},{"time":442000,"text":"These are the Athabasca tar sands, and there's an"},{"time":444000,"text":"enormous amount -- first of mining, the largest"},{"time":447000,"text":"trucks in the world are working here, and then"},{"time":450000,"text":"you've got to pull out this black sludge, which is"},{"time":452000,"text":"basically oil that doesn't flow. It's tied to the"},{"time":455000,"text":"sand. And then you've got to use a lot of steam to"},{"time":457000,"text":"separate it, which only works at today's oil"},{"time":460000,"text":"prices."}]},{"cues":[{"time":462000,"text":"Coal. Coal turns out to be virtually the same"},{"time":466000,"text":"stuff. It is probably plants, except that these"},{"time":470000,"text":"have been burned and crushed under pressure."},{"time":474000,"text":"So you take something like this, you burn it, you"},{"time":476000,"text":"put it under pressure, and likely as not, you get"},{"time":478000,"text":"this. Although, again, I stress: we don't know."},{"time":481000,"text":"Which is curious as we debate all this stuff. But"},{"time":484000,"text":"as you think of coal, this is what burned wheat"},{"time":487000,"text":"kernels look like. Not entirely unlike coal."}]},{"cues":[{"time":492000,"text":"And of course, coalmines are very dangerous"},{"time":495000,"text":"places because in some of these coalmines, you"},{"time":498000,"text":"get gas. When that gas blows up, people die. So"},{"time":505000,"text":"you're producing a biogas out of coal in some"},{"time":507000,"text":"mines, but not in others."},{"time":510000,"text":"Any place you see a differential, there're some"},{"time":512000,"text":"interesting questions. There's some questions as"},{"time":515000,"text":"to what you should be doing with this stuff. But"},{"time":517000,"text":"again, coal. Maybe the same stuff, maybe the same"},{"time":521000,"text":"system, maybe bioenergy, and you're applying"},{"time":523000,"text":"exactly the same technology."}]},{"cues":[{"time":525000,"text":"Here's your brute force approach. Once you get"},{"time":528000,"text":"through your brute force approach, then you just"},{"time":529000,"text":"rip off whole mountaintops. And you end up with"},{"time":533000,"text":"the single largest source of carbon emissions,"},{"time":536000,"text":"which are coal-fired gas plants. That is probably"},{"time":540000,"text":"not the best use of bioenergy."},{"time":544000,"text":"As you think of what are the alternatives to this"},{"time":546000,"text":"system -- it's important to find alternatives"},{"time":549000,"text":"because it turns out that the U.S. is dwindling in"},{"time":552000,"text":"its petroleum reserves, but it is not dwindling in"},{"time":554000,"text":"its coal reserves, nor is China. There are huge"},{"time":559000,"text":"coal reserves that are sitting out there, and"},{"time":562000,"text":"we've got to start thinking of them as biological"},{"time":564000,"text":"energy, because if we keep treating them as"},{"time":566000,"text":"chemical energy, or engineering energy, we're"},{"time":569000,"text":"going to be in deep doo-doo."}]},{"cues":[{"time":574000,"text":"Gas is a similar issue. Gas is also a biological"},{"time":579000,"text":"product. And as you think of gas, well, you're"},{"time":584000,"text":"familiar with gas. And here's a different way of"},{"time":589000,"text":"mining coal."},{"time":592000,"text":"This is called coal bed methane. Why is this"},{"time":595000,"text":"picture interesting? Because if coal turns out to"},{"time":598000,"text":"be concentrated plant life, the reason why you may"},{"time":602000,"text":"get a differential in gas output between one mine"},{"time":606000,"text":"and another -- the reason why one mine may blow up"},{"time":608000,"text":"and another one may not blow up -- may be because"},{"time":611000,"text":"there's stuff eating that stuff and producing gas."},{"time":617000,"text":"This is a well-known phenomenon. (Laughter) You"},{"time":622000,"text":"eat certain things, you produce a lot of gas. It"},{"time":627000,"text":"may turn out that biological processes in coalmines"},{"time":630000,"text":"have the same process. If that is true, then"},{"time":633000,"text":"one of the ways of getting the energy out of coal"},{"time":635000,"text":"may not be to rip whole mountaintops off, and it"},{"time":639000,"text":"may not be to burn coal. It may be to have stuff"},{"time":643000,"text":"process that coal in a biological fashion as you"},{"time":646000,"text":"did in agriculture."}]},{"cues":[{"time":649000,"text":"That is what bioenergy is. It is not ethanol. It"},{"time":653000,"text":"is not subsidies to a few companies. It is not"},{"time":656000,"text":"importing corn into Iowa because you've built so"},{"time":659000,"text":"many of these ethanol plants. It is beginning to"},{"time":662000,"text":"understand the transition that occurred in"},{"time":664000,"text":"agriculture, from brute force into biological"},{"time":667000,"text":"force. And in the measure that you can do that,"},{"time":669000,"text":"you can clean some stuff, and you can clean it"},{"time":670000,"text":"pretty quickly."},{"time":672000,"text":"We already have some indicators of productivity on"},{"time":675000,"text":"this stuff. OK, if you put steam into coal fields"},{"time":679000,"text":"or petroleum fields that have been running for"},{"time":682000,"text":"decades, you can get a really substantial"},{"time":684000,"text":"increase, like an eight-fold increase, in your"},{"time":687000,"text":"output. This is just the beginning stages of this"},{"time":691000,"text":"stuff."}]},{"cues":[{"time":692000,"text":"And as you think of biomaterials, this guy -- who"},{"time":694000,"text":"did part of the sequencing of the human genome,"},{"time":697000,"text":"who just doubled the databases of genes and"},{"time":699000,"text":"proteins known on earth by sailing around the"},{"time":701000,"text":"world -- has been thinking about how you structure"},{"time":705000,"text":"this. And there's a series of smart people"},{"time":706000,"text":"thinking about this. And they've been putting"},{"time":709000,"text":"together companies like Synthetic Genomics, like,"},{"time":711000,"text":"a Cambria, like Codon, and what those companies are"},{"time":715000,"text":"trying to do is to think of, how do you apply"},{"time":718000,"text":"biological principles to avoid brute force?"},{"time":722000,"text":"Think of it in the following terms. Think of it as"},{"time":725000,"text":"beginning to program stuff for specific purposes."},{"time":729000,"text":"Think of the cell as a hardware. Think of the"},{"time":732000,"text":"genes as a software. And in the measure that you"},{"time":735000,"text":"begin to think of life as code that is"},{"time":738000,"text":"interchangeable, that can become energy, that can"},{"time":741000,"text":"become food, that can become fiber, that can"},{"time":743000,"text":"become human beings, that can become a whole"},{"time":745000,"text":"series of things, then you've got to shift your"},{"time":748000,"text":"approach as to how you're going to structure and"},{"time":750000,"text":"deal and think about energy in a very different"},{"time":754000,"text":"way."}]},{"cues":[{"time":756000,"text":"What are the first principles of this stuff and"},{"time":758000,"text":"where are we heading? This is one of the gentle"},{"time":761000,"text":"giants on the planet. He's one of the nicest human"},{"time":764000,"text":"beings you've ever met. His name is Hamilton"},{"time":767000,"text":"Smith. He won the Nobel for figuring out how to"},{"time":770000,"text":"cut genes -- something called restriction enzymes."},{"time":775000,"text":"He was at Hopkins when he did this, and he's such"},{"time":777000,"text":"a modest guy that the day he won, his mother"},{"time":780000,"text":"called him and said, \"I didn't realize there was"},{"time":783000,"text":"another Ham Smith at Hopkins. Do you know he just"},{"time":785000,"text":"won the Nobel?\" (Laughter) I mean, that was Mom,"},{"time":793000,"text":"but anyway, this guy is just a class act. You find"},{"time":796000,"text":"him at the bench every single day, working on a"},{"time":799000,"text":"pipette and building stuff. And one of the things"},{"time":803000,"text":"this guy just built are these things."}]},{"cues":[{"time":805000,"text":"What is this? This is the first transplant of"},{"time":807000,"text":"naked DNA, where you take an entire DNA operating"},{"time":810000,"text":"system out of one cell, insert it into a different"},{"time":813000,"text":"cell, and have that cell boot up as a separate"},{"time":816000,"text":"species. That's one month old. You will see stuff"},{"time":822000,"text":"in the next month that will be just as important"},{"time":824000,"text":"as this stuff."},{"time":826000,"text":"And as you think about this stuff and what the"},{"time":828000,"text":"implications of this are, we're going to start not"},{"time":831000,"text":"just converting ethanol from corn with very high"},{"time":836000,"text":"subsidies. We're going to start thinking about"},{"time":838000,"text":"biology entering energy. It is very expensive to"},{"time":843000,"text":"process this stuff, both in economic terms and in"},{"time":847000,"text":"energy terms."}]},{"cues":[{"time":849000,"text":"This is what accumulates in the tar sands of"},{"time":851000,"text":"Alberta. These are sulfur blocks. Because as you"},{"time":855000,"text":"separate that petroleum from the sand, and use an"},{"time":858000,"text":"enormous amount of energy inside that vapor --"},{"time":862000,"text":"steam to separate this stuff -- you also have to"},{"time":864000,"text":"separate out the sulfur. The difference between"},{"time":866000,"text":"light crude and heavy crude -- well, it's about 14"},{"time":869000,"text":"bucks a barrel. That's why you're building these"},{"time":872000,"text":"pyramids of sulfur blocks. And by the way, the"},{"time":874000,"text":"scale on these things is pretty large."}]},{"cues":[{"time":878000,"text":"Now, if you can take part of the energy content"},{"time":880000,"text":"out of doing this, you reduce the system, and you"},{"time":884000,"text":"really do start applying biological principles to"},{"time":886000,"text":"energy. This has to be a bridge to the point where"},{"time":891000,"text":"you can get to wind, to the point where you can"},{"time":893000,"text":"get to solar, to the point where you can get to"},{"time":895000,"text":"nuclear -- and hopefully you won't build the next"},{"time":898000,"text":"nuclear plant on a beautiful seashore next to an"},{"time":901000,"text":"earthquake fault. (Laughter) Just a thought."}]},{"cues":[{"time":910000,"text":"But in the meantime, for the next decade at least,"},{"time":914000,"text":"the name of the game is hydrocarbons. And be that"},{"time":917000,"text":"oil, be that gas, be that coal, this is what we're"},{"time":921000,"text":"dealing with. And before I make this talk too"},{"time":925000,"text":"long, here's what's happening in the current"},{"time":930000,"text":"energy system."},{"time":932000,"text":"86 percent of the energy we consume are"},{"time":934000,"text":"hydrocarbons. That means 86 percent of the stuff we're"},{"time":937000,"text":"consuming are probably processed plants and"},{"time":940000,"text":"amoebas and the rest of the stuff. And there's a"},{"time":943000,"text":"role in here for conservation. There's a role in"},{"time":945000,"text":"here for alternative stuff, but we've also got to"},{"time":947000,"text":"get that other portion right."},{"time":950000,"text":"How we deal with that other portion is our bridge"},{"time":952000,"text":"to the future. And as we think of this bridge to"},{"time":955000,"text":"the future, one of the things you should ponder"},{"time":958000,"text":"is: we are leaving about two-thirds of the oil today"},{"time":961000,"text":"inside those wells. So we're spending an enormous"},{"time":964000,"text":"amount of money and leaving most of the energy"},{"time":967000,"text":"down there. Which, of course, requires more energy"},{"time":970000,"text":"to go out and get energy. The ratios become"},{"time":973000,"text":"idiotic by the time you get to ethanol. It may"},{"time":975000,"text":"even be a one-to-one ratio on the energy input and"},{"time":978000,"text":"the energy output. That is a stupid way of"},{"time":981000,"text":"managing this system."}]},{"cues":[{"time":984000,"text":"Last point, last graph. One of the things that"},{"time":988000,"text":"we've got to do is to stabilize oil prices. This"},{"time":992000,"text":"is what oil prices look like, OK?"},{"time":994000,"text":"This is a very bad system because what happens is"},{"time":997000,"text":"your hurdle rate gets set very low. People come up"},{"time":1000000,"text":"with really smart ideas for solar panels, or for"},{"time":1003000,"text":"wind, or for something else, and then guess what?"},{"time":1005000,"text":"The oil price goes through the floor. That company"},{"time":1007000,"text":"goes out of business, and then you can bring the"},{"time":1009000,"text":"oil price back up."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1011000,"text":"So if I had one closing and modest suggestion,"},{"time":1015000,"text":"let's set a stable oil price in Europe and the"},{"time":1017000,"text":"United States. How do you do that? Well, let's put"},{"time":1022000,"text":"a tax on oil that is a non-revenue tax, and it"},{"time":1024000,"text":"basically says for the next 20 years, the price of"},{"time":1028000,"text":"oil will be -- whatever you want, 35 bucks, 40"},{"time":1031000,"text":"bucks. If the OPEC price falls below that, we tax"},{"time":1035000,"text":"it. If the OPEC price goes above that, the tax"},{"time":1038000,"text":"goes away."},{"time":1041000,"text":"What does that do for entrepreneurs? What does it"},{"time":1042000,"text":"do for companies? It tells people, if you can"},{"time":1045000,"text":"produce energy for less than 35 bucks a barrel, or"},{"time":1048000,"text":"less than 40 bucks a barrel, or less than 50 bucks"},{"time":1050000,"text":"a barrel -- let's debate it -- you will have a"},{"time":1054000,"text":"business. But let's not put people through this"},{"time":1056000,"text":"cycle where it doesn't pay to research because"},{"time":1059000,"text":"your company will go out of business as OPEC"},{"time":1061000,"text":"drives alternatives and keeps bioenergy from"},{"time":1064000,"text":"happening. Thank you."}]}]}